Objects:
-every component in javascript is object including function,
strings and Numbers.
-we normally use object-literals or costructor functions to create objects

Encapsulation:

-Methods and Properties are hidden from the rest of other apps or modules
-Abstratc specific set fo functionalities an object

Inheritance:

-Advnatages of these concepts that can allow us to build a project
with reusable code ,scalabale architecture and abstracted functionalities

Instance:

-instance is an implementation of a function.
-It is a copy of function or an object

function Tree(typeof){};

//bananaTree is an instance of Tree

var bananTree=new Tree("banana");
